  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Relief for Hearing Impaired and Disabled Syrian Refugees in Jordan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Overall Goal: To improve the quality of life for Syrian refugees and vulnerable Jordanians with hearing, sight, and mobility disabilities through the delivery of high quality diagnostic, rehabilitation, and education programs.

Objective 1: To increase Syrian refugee and host community capability to screen, assess, and refer disabled cases for treatment through disability training for 60 Community Based Rehabilitation Workers (CBRWs).

Objective 2: High quality diagnostic and rehabilitation services provided to 594 Syrian and 396 Jordanian vulnerable and disabled children and youth.

Objective 3: 594 Syrian refugee and 396 vulnerable Jordanian parents plus 2,500 members of the community have increased knowledge and awareness of disability and referral pathways.</narrative>
  </description>
